Great Wall Motor, Li & Fung, Stella: Hong Kong Stocks Preview

-- B y   K a n a   N i s h i z a w a
-- 
2011-04-12T00:37:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/great-wall-motor-li-fung-stella-hong-kong-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
significant price changes in Hong Kong trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses. Share prices are as of the last close.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  fell 0.4 percent to 24,303.07. The Hang
Seng  China  Enterprises Index, which tracks so-called H shares of
Chinese companies, rose 0.2 percent to 13,684.06.  Great Wall Motor Co. (2333 HK): The mainland carmaker will
recall 4,685 vehicles from April 15 because they used tires from
Kumho Tire Co., which were made with more recycled rubber than
allowed, according to a statement on the General Administration
of Quality Supervision, Inspection and Quarantine’s website. The
shares rose 0.1 percent to HK$13.90.  Hutchison Whampoa Ltd. (13)  (13 HK): The company said it will
pay 1.62 billion yuan ($248 million) for land in Shanghai’s Zhao
Xiang town to build homes. The stock declined 0.7 percent to
HK$92.40.  Industrial & Commercial Bank of China (1398)  Ltd. (1398 HK): The
world’s biggest-lender by market value said it plans to open a
bank in  Brazil , extending its reach to Latin America’s largest
economy after expanding in  Europe  and the U.S. The stock
increased 0.3 percent to HK$6.65.  Li & Fung Ltd. (494)  (494 HK): The biggest supplier to retailers
including Wal-Mart Stores Inc. said it plans a share split,
dividing each existing share into two. The stock declined 0.3
percent to HK$40.40.  Stella International Holdings Ltd. (1836)  (1836 HK): The footwear
maker and retailer with outlets in China said its unaudited
revenue for the three months ended March 31 rose about 22
percent to $272.9 million from the same period a year earlier.
The stock gained 0.7 percent to HK$17.58  To contact the reporter on this story:
